Run the program first without GDB to see the raw crash: ./target — note the "Segmentation fault" message.
Inside GDB, after the crash, 'backtrace' (or 'bt') shows the full call stack from main down to the crash point.
'frame N' switches to frame N from the backtrace. 'frame 0' is where the crash happened. 'list' shows the source lines around it.
'info registers' shows the CPU state at crash time. Look at rip (instruction pointer) and the argument registers.
